            <div id="concept-analysis">
                <h3>About the Game</h3>
                <p>Tile-matching games such as Candy Crush and Bejeweled have been played and loved by millions for decades. A player is shown an 8x8 grid randomly filled with differently colored items, one item in each grid space. The player can swap any one item with another adjacent item. When matching three or more of the same item in one line, the matched items disappear and the player is awarded points. The award is greater the larger the matched group is. There is no win or loss condition; the playerâ€™s goal is simply to maximize the number of points earned in the least amount of turns. Kitty Combos will be a cat-themed tile-matching game with score-tracking and an online leaderboard.</p>
            </div>
            <br />

            <div id="scope">
                <h3>Features</h3>
                <p>The project has several main mechanics:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Fully interactable board</li>
                    <li>Tile images sourced from API</li>
                    <li>Tile swapping with restrictions</li>
                    <li>Decreasing turn counter</li>
                    <li>Score calculation</li>
                    <li>Leaderbard powered by database to host scores</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
            <br />

            <div id="future">
                <h3>Kitty Combos V2</h3>
                <p>We brainstormed several ideas for expanding our game in the future, given we have adequate time and funding.</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>In the future, we'd like to include levels where tiles populate various board shapes and sizes.</li>
                    <li>Implement a timer.</li>
                    <li>Reduce turn count.</li>
                    <li>A "frantic" tile mode using gifs instead of images.</li>
                    <li>Check for potential matches to make sure the board is solvable.</li>
                    <li>Implement responsive board size.</li>
                    <li>Add keyboard/controller support for accessibility and ADA compliance.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
